reviews.review_text: Slow How can a digital master audience be slow?  I'm not sure I understand unless there is an analog generation in here but this recording sounds like the band collectively hit a nitrous balloon before they started singing.

not slow, just at 16 48K this was mastered at 48K and if you try to convert to 44.1 it will sound slow.

this is an amazing AUD recording of what might be the last rippin' dead show.

Best sounding copy of great show. My favorite show, start to finish, of Fall 94. This Mk4 FOB sounds great. Easily the best of the aud sources.  You want this one. I had no problem burning to disk.  I think a lot of burning programs automatically convert 48k to 44.1k.
